Etymology[edit]

nāvis (“ship”) +‎ -igō

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈnaː.wi.ɡoː/, [ˈnaː.wɪ.ɡoː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈna.vi.ɡo/, [ˈnaː.vi.ɡɔ]

Verb[edit]

nāvigō (present infinitive nāvigāre, perfect active nāvigāvī, supine nāvigātum); first conjugation

  1. I sail, navigate, seafare
